The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, May 06, 2004 				 Beauty is truth, truth beauty...
As part of the 30th anniversary celebrations of Gorky Sadan, its cultural department hosts Celebration of Life, an exhibition of photographs by Bibek Guha. Celebrating all that is good and beautiful about our world, it reminds us of the possibility of finding true peace and happiness in the world, in spite of all the hatred and cruelty that have ravaged it. Realizing the importance of communicating with nature, Guhas photographs symbolize his conviction that proximity with nature can restore to mankind his human values and his capacity to love selflessly. Through images of sparkling clarity, he expresses his own love for truth and honesty, which he believes can cleanse the universe of its evils, and once again make the world a beautiful place to live in.																								Event: An exhibition of photographs by Bibek Guha																								When: Till May 7; 4 pm - 7 pm																								Where: Gorky Sadan
